Attention Parent(s)/Guardian(s): HDC Administration is working on a plan for the start of the school year. Please stay tuned for information to be sent out by July 20th. We are waiting as long as possible to ensure that we have the most up-to-date information in regards to COVID-19. After our Board of Education meeting on July 15th, we will send out information to the staff first and then information out to parents and students. The plan is still to have in-person learning, beginning on Thursday, August 13th with guidelines and precautions put into place. I know everyone is anxious to know exactly what will take place, please understand we are working with the health departments to implement a plan that will work for our district.

*2020 Graduates - Information about graduation, rehearsal, and protocols will be mailed out to you by July 6th.

Take Care, Stay Safe and Go Jags! - Mr. Ernst

The final order for 2020 Howells-Dodge Yearbooks will be completed this week. The
price is $45 or $48 for a yearbook with your name printed on the front. If you would like
to order, checks should be made payable to Howells-Dodge Consolidated Schools and
mailed to Marla Prusa, Howells-Dodge Consolidated Schools, 418 May Street, Howells,
NE 68641. 2020 Yearbooks will be delivered in August.
Also, students, staff and parents, please feel free to send any photos of what you are
doing during this COVID-19 school closing for the yearbook. Whether you are
completing enrichment activities for school, doing chores, playing video games, or
working out, we would like to include pictures of you in the 2020 yearbook!
You can email any photos to mprusa@hdcjags.org and they will be shared with the
yearbook staff members.

Attention - Reminder:
The 7-12 building will be open from 8am-4pm tomorrow, Friday, March 20th to get your books, Chromebooks, and school materials during the closure. All students need to make an effort to pick their items up. 7-12 students, If you live in Dodge and need a ride, the bus will leave Dodge at 8am and then immediately return after items are gathered in Howells. We want you to clean out your gym lockers as well, so we can do a deep clean of the whole facility. If you fail to pick up your things, Mr. Ernst and Mr. Fischer will make personal deliveries to your home. You need to make every effort to show up or call at the school. Elementary pick-up for HDC elementary students will be able to come in at both Howells and Dodge from 3:00 to 6:00 p.m.
